===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[abandoning]], or the state of being abandoned; total [[desertion]]; [[relinquishment]]. {{defdate|Late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=2}}</ref>
#* {{quote-book|year=1790-1800|passage=To what are we reserved? An ''adequate'' compensation "for the sacrifice of powers the most nearly connected with us;"— an ''adequate'' compensation "for the direct or indirect annexation to France ot all the ports of the continent, from Dunkirk to Hamburgh;"— an ''adequate'' compensation "for the '''abandonment''' of the independence of Europe!"|author=[[w:Edmund Burke|Edmund Burke]]|title=[[w:Letters on a Regicide Peace|Letters on a Regicide Peace]]}}
# The voluntary leaving of a person to whom one is bound by a special relation, as a wife, husband or child; desertion.
#: ''Since he left her, she's suing him for divorce on grounds of '''abandonment'''.''
# An abandoned [[building]] or [[structure]].
#: ''High-profile '''abandonments''' are harder to infiltrate for urban explorers due to their heightened security.''
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} The relinquishment of a right, claim, or privilege; relinquishment of right to secure a [[patent]] by an inventor; relinquishment of [[copyright]] by an author. {{defdate|Early 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|legal|lang=en}} The relinquishment by the [[insured]] to the [[underwriters]] of what may remain of the property insured after a loss or damage by a [[peril]] insured against. {{defdate|Early 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The [[cessation]] of service on a particular segment of the lines of a [[common carrier]], as granted by a government agency.
# A [[refusal]] to [[receive]] [[freight]] so [[damaged]] in [[transit]] as to be [[worthless]] and [[render]] [[carrier]] [[liable]] for its [[value]].
# The self-surrender to an outside influence. {{defdate|Mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# [[abandon|Abandon]]; careless freedom or ease; surrender to one's emotions. {{defdate|Mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-book|title=Heart: In the Studio|author=Jake Brown|year=2008|passage=Roger, in terms of the strengths he brought to the band, was wild '''abandonment'''. So if Howard was in the pocket, Roger was bouncing off the walls, and Nancy was somewhere in the middle.}}

